{
  "stem": "9899.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But when my uncle explained to him that he would do it for the good of humanity, then my grandfather Mark agreed and gave him a written permission, as it was used to do in those years.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so Joel Karl, who was the eldest of the brothers, went to Vienna and began his study in medicine.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In later years, he became a very famous doctor and was director of a sanatorium in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But in 1938, he was told that because he was a Jew he was not allowed to practice medicine anymore and was asked to leave the country.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The only country that gave him a visa, because he did apply to several ones, including the United States and other places, England, where everybody refused him, but Peru gave him a visa.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And with a friend, they left in 1938 Vienna and traveled to Lima, where he established himself as a doctor.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "On the other brothers and sisters, in 1938 all the family was well, prosperous.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They each had work.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They each belonged to different societies.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And although they heard about this things going on in Germany, it was so remote from us that nobody was afraid and didn't really know what was happening.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Towards the end of 1938, the Russians came in, and the state would ask for a little while.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But the Germans had declared war on Poland in 1939, and so the Russians left, and the Germans were approaching slowly but surely.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And after the invasion of Poland, it took them two years to reach us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But when they came in into Lemberg, they came with a fierce hand, and all the persecutions and the nightmares began.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
